page.title: 10CLUBS_CORNWALL CONSERVATION
page.content: I am in the Cornwall Fox Club.Members receive a regular newsletter.They are called the C.N.T.S.which stands for the {Cornwall Nature Trust Society.} They have outings.For example on 30th June my family and I went to investigate bats and moths.This is what happened.A man had a bat detector which helps to discover bats.We saw some bats flying under a viaduct.The bat detector senses the noise of the bats wings.I like the Fox Club very much.Some other things we have done include_ planting marram grass on the local dunes, a trip to Victoria Gardens,Truro,for a walk and pond study, a visit to Coverack,for a beach study. There are about 50 people in the club. The leader is Mr.David Lewis.
